<h2>&#x221a;div</h2><p>
<i>see </i><b><a href="dIv1.htm">dīv1</a></b></p><p>
No root &#x221a;<b>div</b> 'shine' exists as such in the language, except so far as it may be inferable from the noun <b>dív</b> or <b>dyú</b> V.+, <b>divít</b> RV., and the (in that case, secondary) root <b>dyut</b>.  With all these the root <b>dīv</b> 'play' has nothing to do.</p></body>
